1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:07,460
What we have to do is create a project using Visual Studio 2022.

2
00:00:08,029 --> 00:00:16,670
I have opened Visual Studio 2022 here and I will select create a new project on the left hand side here.

3
00:00:16,670 --> 00:00:23,030
I will have recent project templates, but what we want to do here is search for MVC.

4
00:00:23,390 --> 00:00:27,740
And with that we should get ASP.NET Core Web app.

5
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:32,030
Now the project we want to work on is MVC application.

6
00:00:32,030 --> 00:00:36,200
So make sure to select the one with Model View and Controller.

7
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:42,440
There is also a web app without MVC that uses razor pages.

8
00:00:42,590 --> 00:00:44,300
We do not want that.

9
00:00:45,350 --> 00:00:51,590
We will give our project a name of bulky web, location wherever you want to save it.

10
00:00:51,590 --> 00:00:53,630
And then we need a solution.

11
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:55,820
Name. now solution name,

12
00:00:55,820 --> 00:01:01,670
I will keep that as bulky because in there we will have multiple project.

13
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:05,390
With that configured, let me hit the next button.

14
00:01:05,810 --> 00:01:09,320
The framework that we want to use is .net eight.

15
00:01:09,350 --> 00:01:12,530
We will select that, authentication type.

16
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:15,410
We will be adding authentication later on.

17
00:01:15,410 --> 00:01:22,010
But right now we want to keep things super simple and then we will add on to our project.

18
00:01:22,460 --> 00:01:27,560
So right now we will keep that as none configure for HTTPS.

19
00:01:27,590 --> 00:01:30,320
That looks good and we will not check that.

20
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:32,630
Do not use top level statements.

21
00:01:32,630 --> 00:01:37,880
It is just adding the using statements at the top and it is not that important.

22
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:42,230
That is why we can just ignore that and hit the create button.

23
00:01:43,210 --> 00:01:48,580
With the click of that button, the magic happens and your project is created.

24
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:54,340
I will explore all the files and folders that are being created by default.

25
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:58,050
But before that, let me add this to source control.

26
00:01:59,370 --> 00:02:02,240
I have already signed in to my git repo.

27
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:04,350
So that is coming along.

28
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:05,790
Repository name.

29
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:09,330
Let me call that bulky underscore MVC.

30
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:17,160
I will make that a private repository for now, but once the course is launched, I will convert that

31
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:19,650
to be a public repository.

32
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:24,890
With that configured, let me hit, create and push button.

33
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,630
And perfect.

34
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:28,950
We have two outgoing changes.

35
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:30,560
Let me push them.

36
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,190
Perfect.

37
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:38,950
So we have created our project and we have committed our code to the git repo.

